    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Dulwich</placeName>
                    <date>March the 7th</date>
                    <salute>Dear Henslow</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I regret that your letter should have remained so long unanswered but my absence from London must plead my excuse. You are correct in supposing I had no vote for the University, both my brother &amp; myself have taken our names off the Boards.</p>
                  <p>If I should ever come to Cambridge you may rely on my finding you out &amp; I trust you will not stay in London without paying me a visit at Dulwich</p>
                  <p>believe me yrs very truly</p>
                  <p>Jefferys T. Allen</p>
                  <p>Have votes for Lord Palmerston only</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
